Text: Over the years I've learned that it is better to busy yourself with things you can control rather than worry about things you cannot.
A hot meal will be waiting for you when you return. Understood?
It falls to you and I, Coultenet, to ensure those imperial dogs set no foot in the Rising Stones. The tragedy of the Waking Sands must never be repeated!
Quite right, Hoary. Yet I fear we two alone could not resist a full-scale assault. Mayhap we had best draft a plan of evacuation, should the worst come to the worst...
My father has agreed to take care of Yozan for me. The children need role models, and we must do whatever is in our power to provide them.
I am ready... Hozan, are your preparations complete?
Doware and Hozan are about to take up their posts. It seems even the children are starting to understand the gravity of the situation.
Hey... Hey... I jus' gotta say... Yer a─hic─a pretty─hic─a... A... Yer all right.
What you two do is your own business. Don't say I didn't warn you!
I do not fault Ser Aymeric for being less than forthcoming with his beliefs. Not even the highborn are beyond the reach of the inquisition.
True, young leaders can be more amenable to new ideas. Then again, their lack of experience and influence can hinder their ability to enact reforms.
Trying to tumble the table now, are we? Don't give up yet, boy! Yda! Line 'em up!
There's little fortune and far less fame in being a receptionist. But one must be realistic!
...Also, it would seem that I was grossly misinformed regarding the average earnings of a street performer.
Ah, forgive me, <split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)>... I thought I had prepared enough meals for everyone, but the others were most hungry...
Calm yourshelf, Coultenet! It'sh jusht a little ship after practish... Clearsh out the cobwebsh no end!
A sip before practice, a sip after practice, and all too often a sip during practice! I do believe Moenbryda is having quite the bad influence on you.
Our stocks of wine have nearly run dry. That Sharlayan scholar is drinking us out of house and home!
<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>! 'Tis always a pleasure! In Gridania for the Alliance meeting, I presume? So am I!
My fellow 2nd Unit Braves and I are here to provide additional security during the Alliance meeting, <If(PlayerParameter(4))>milady<Else/>sir</If>!
I'm here on special security detail. And by “special,” I mean “dull as hells.” Nary a soul comes through this gate. \\<yawn>
We Braves're meant to be forerunners for a united Grand Company. Sounds impressive, aye, but guard duty's guard duty, no matter how fancy yer duds look.
We 2nd Unit Braves are in Gridania on special security detail. Any suspicious activity will be swiftly nipped in the bud!
Hear ye, hear ye! The Continental Circus is in town! Steel yourself for a pants-soilingly terrifying All Saints' Wake experience!
Ah, if it isn't my favorite adventurer. Thanks again for helping us here in Gridania. If you're not busy, I'd appreciate it if you could lend a hand to the festivities elsewhere as well.
I'm given to understand that the parade in Ul'dah was a resounding success. Then why is it still so...peaceful?
Did you know? The warding lanterns are crafted in the likeness of the Great Gourd, the archfiend who is said to appear during All Saints' Wake. You learn something new every day, eh?
I hadn't reckoned on the lanterns getting removed. And I poured my heart and soul into them... \\<sigh>
My fellow troupe members report that the parade in Ul'dah was a runaway success. If only my lanterns weren't thrown out, we might all be celebrating right now... \\<sigh>
This All Saints' Wake, the Continental Circus is hosting a splendidly spooky parade right here in Ul'dah! Participation is open to everyone with a penchant for having fun and making mischief!
The charm will take effect any moment now, I'm sure of it. Like...now!
...Or not? Well, worrying my little wings over it won't make it happen any faster. I'll just keep on hosting the parade in the meantime.
If you come into any demonic cookies, be sure to bring them to me. I'll furnish you with fabulous All Saints' Wake-themed prizes in return!
Rorojaru's renounced the pursuit of profit─he pitched up at the guild to seek schooling as a fledgling fisherman. Am I right in reckoning he surrendered that star–spangled subligar to you?
If so, I've a word of warning: be wary of wearing it in the water. The fish flock to bask in its brilliance, and the buggers'll bite.
To confront Iceheart once more, with full knowledge of her talents... My friend, I am truly grateful for everything you have done, as is every man with knowledge of your deeds.
Would that every Ishgardian could know. Yet even Master Alphinaud agrees that some tales are too dangerous to spread.
My analysis of the specimen continues. What happened to those pirates in Sastasha is quite fascinating...from a purely scientific standpoint, of course.
Ah, it's grand to have cause to ply my trade again! I'll work twice as hard as ever to make Hihira's dreams come true─and if I earn a few gil for myself along the way, well, what's the harm in that?
Hm, not too bad, are they? The twins, I mean. Well, you're not dead and you're not weeping, are you? I'd call that a win.
Truth be told, it's the odd ones you remember most fondly. That's what makes it an adventure, aye. A touch of danger in everything, even the client...
Reyner and I, we've known each other since I was first starting out as a culinarian. We hardly see each other these days, though.

I've invited him here a bunch of times, but the man's married to his duty─“another time,” he always tells me. If he ever manages to pay me visit, though, you can be sure I'll whip him up a meal fit for royalty.

The White Rams hunt the Ixal─we live to spring on the little birds and snap their wee necks! If those whose lives I once spared even think of setting foot in the Twelveswood again, they'll answer to meow!
...Answer to meow. To meeeeeeow. Aaargh! I'll kill them, alright!?
I shan't lie, <split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)>, the going is slow, and I've barely enough help to brew remedy for all the sick here.
Still, I feel I've taken a step on the road towards saving the ailing─and if my father can be persuaded to walk it beside me, all the better.
Always regretted never sayin' good-bye to Myrtha. Ain't many who find them they lost, an' I'm lucky to have learned she's alive.
So, I've decided to share my good fortune, by givin' the money left over from our ceruleum venture to the refugee children. Maybe their smiles'll turn some bad folk good, eh?
Do you know how much I lost speculating on those blasted rumors? If ever I hear the word ceruleum again, it will be too soon... \\<sniffle>

My dear <If(PlayerParameter(4))>madam<Else/>sir</If>, Syntgoht's Sundries has survived the ceruleum crash─in no small part due to your patronage. I do hope your employer sold his futures before the prices came tumbling down.
Ye lookin' to head inside?
All day, every day, we toil here at the docks, with naught but the sound of pounding hammers to mark the passage of time. If you've any tall tales to share, I'd be glad for the diversion.
How're you finding the job, <If(PlayerParameter(4))>lass<Else/>lad</If>? I've been so long a shipwright now that I twirl a hammer far better than I ever did the shortblades...

Hither comes the tamer of the terrible─and toothsome─Nepto Dragon! You are an authority among anglers, upon this all are agreed, but if you would fain fish at the forefront forever, never must you rest your reel-hand!
Say what you want about our many-faced thief, he hasn't lost his flair for the dramatic. With these promises of justice, doubtless he's won over a whole new legion of fans.
Did you know that the Mythril Eye sometimes gets fan letters addressed to the many-faced thief? Just goes to show how my articles have won over the hearts of the people!

Now, as much as I'd love to stand here and chat all <If(LessThan(PlayerParameter(11),12))><If(LessThan(PlayerParameter(11),4))>night<Else/>day</If><Else/><If(LessThan(PlayerParameter(11),17))>day<Else/>night</If></If>, I've got some relics to research!
Would it kill them to station me a few yalms closer to the action? Gods forbid I actually get to enjoy the tourney after all my hard work...
Since the day I became a shinobi, my every action has been dictated by one mission or another.
Now there is no duty that calls me. At first, the freedom was overwhelming.
But I have found peace with it. I will take the time to see the world, and honor the memory of my fallen comrades...
The heretics' aggression grows by leaps and bounds, but we of House Fortemps are not wont to cower behind our walls.
Is it true? The heretics...they summoned Shiva? And you laid her low? Fury take me...
Aye, it's past time we take the fight to the heretics! Why it's taken so long, I don't even know.
I heard about Snowcloak─what you faced there, I mean. I'm glad you're on our side, Scion.
Lookin' to join us in the shadows, are ye? Bene luck to ye, then.
The name's Bochard. I might be the eldest rogue left standin', but I'm happy to leave the guildmasterin' to young Jacke.
I won't be givin' ye jobs or aught like that, but I can learn ye a thing or two about twirlin' them stabbers. All in good time, though, <If(PlayerParameter(4))>dove<Else/>colt</If>, all in good time.
All right, then, <If(PlayerParameter(4))>dove<Else/>colt</If>? I expect ye've mastered the first step in the dance o' daggers, have ye? Aye, the Spinnin' Edge.

Simple, direct, an' sets ye up for a fierce Gust Slash. That's where ye spin yer leg around quick enough to whip up a wind...then dart in to stick yer mark while he's wonderin' where that breeze come from.

All right, then, <If(PlayerParameter(4))>dove<Else/>colt</If>? I hear ye've been practicing yer skulkin' skills good and proper. Keep to the shadows and seal yer gob shut, and you'll be able to hop the twig no matter who's got their glazes out for ye.
Don't get too comfortable, though, eh? No one's going to be there to lend ye their daddles if ye get whiddled out by the guards.

Lend me your wattles, <If(PlayerParameter(4))>dove<Else/>colt</If>. Now, there's no sure thing quite like skulkin' up behind a cull in the darkmans and stickin' him in the neck while he's none the wiser. But that's not always an easy task, an' that's why it'd serve ye well to learn how to toss your stabbers.
Keep yer glazes on yer mark, hold your fambles steady, and ye'll be a dimber damber dagger tosser in no time. But don't take my word for it. Go try yer fams.
All right, then, <If(PlayerParameter(4))>dove<Else/>colt</If>? I hear Jacke learned ye how to Mug a cove. Ah, that skill were more valued in the days when they called us Upright Thieves...
Pirates was proper stubborn back then, see, an' ye had to know how to prise bitten goods from their cold bloody daddles.
All right, then, <If(PlayerParameter(4))>dove<Else/>colt</If>? Not neglectin' yer Trick Attack, are ye? Click a cull from an angle where he don't see it comin' an' ye can save yerself a longer scrap.
Aye, it's a dirty move, but a cove don't concern <If(PlayerParameter(4))>herself<Else/>himself</If> with “fair” when <If(PlayerParameter(4))>she's<Else/>he's</If> aimin' to get a job done.

All right, then, <If(PlayerParameter(4))>dove<Else/>colt</If>? Whid 'round the guild says you was in on the job what saved half the bloody city from slidin' into the sea. Don't reckon there's aught this old cove has left to teach ye...
Ye've learned all me dance steps, an' it's up to you how ye string 'em together. Hells, I expect the next time ye walk in, ye'll have a lesson or two for me!
When Master Mutamix first showed me materia, he lit a fire within me. Imagine─all the spiritual energy swirling about the realm, harnessed in physical form! What awe-inspiring power!
Yes, yesss, I shall become Master Mutamix's right hand, and learn all the secrets of materia! All, you hear me!
Ah, the day I become Master Mutamix's right hand is nigh! All that bars the way to my rightful place is Hubairtin.
But his days as the Bonfire's genius are numbered. In this game of materia we play, I shall be victorious!
Where've they gotten─ Oi! What're you looking at?
Oh, hello there. We're just watching over our cart.
Only dockhands are authorized to enter the storehouse. Be on your way.
Welcome back, <split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)>. You may enter.

Pray do not mind me, <split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)>─I'm just here to ensure that everything proceeds smoothly.
...You look positively <If(PlayerParameter(4))>radiant<Else/>dashing</If>, by the way!
Ring the eternity bell should you wish to proceed to the next stage of the ceremony. Until that time, the floor is yours, and yours alone.
They say that even Daelic the Bold trembled when he received his Crown of Thorns from the Warden after the Battle of the Thirteen Bends, so I can only imagine the anxiety in your hearts here today.
I can think of, oh, at least one thing you'd be better off doing now than exchanging witty banter with a choir moogle, kupo.

Good <If(LessThan(PlayerParameter(11),12))><If(LessThan(PlayerParameter(11),4))>evening<Else/>morrow</If><Else/><If(LessThan(PlayerParameter(11),17))>day<Else/>evening</If></If>, <If(PlayerParameter(4))>m'lady<Else/>m'lord</If>. I am here to investigate the popular perception of sheep in the Gridanian psyche, to see how best they might one day take their rightful place as lord and protector of the forest.
Mayhap it is because I am a stranger here, but the people of this land seem singularly uninterested in engaging with my survey. \\<sigh> It is most dispiriting...

Since I learned the traveling trader would not be bringing the good news to Gridania, I have tried to spread word of the lamb's deeds myself, but these woodsmen do all but stopple their ears to me. I am starting to believe the sheep is simply not in their blood.

They claim that a flock of lambs would gnaw the roots of their beloved trees, and “anger the elementals,” of all things... Still, I will not let their rustic superstitions hold me back. Where there is a will, there is a way!
\\<cough> \\<cough> Pardon me. The fleece on my helm seems to soak up the dust, and then drop it in my face. The Force will need regular shearing if it is to succeed in Thanalan...

But tell me, adventurer: are you a sheep fancier? I mean no offense by it─I am one myself. Should you be interested in learning more about sheep, please speak with my superior, the hitsuji bugyo. You will find him in Limsa Lominsa, leading the Heavensturn festivities.
It is only a matter of time before the Brass Blades make contact, and I make my very first sale. They'll be here soon... Any moment now...
...Why do they not contact me!? Do you think I should go to them? No, no─remember what they told you at Blade headquarters: “Don't call on us, we'll call on you.”
I have come from the Far East, to show you La Nosceans how to celebrate Heavensturn. I must admit, I braced myself for pirates and cutpurses, but find myself most braced by this refreshing sea air!
And yet, how doubly stimulating it would be if this air resounded with the bleating of sheep! Do you not agree, <If(PlayerParameter(4))>m'lady<Else/>m'lord</If>?

Word of your victory travels fast, comrade. Each boat that sets in from Aleport brings fresh whisperings of the sheep that brought peace to the town. Gossip has it that even the boot-faced father has been able to hold the baby without triggering another downpour.
But if the mother and father both have their hands full with the child, how do they propose to spread word of the Fleece Force? These people and their priorities, I tell you!
The entire staff of The Raven stands in support of the Adventurers' Guild and its marvelous Starlight Celebration! Show your Starlight spirit, and contribute in any way you can!
I hear you have pledged to assist the celebrant with the running of the Starlight Celebration. As a professional journalist I feel qualified to say that's wonderful news!
I hope you are enjoying the celebration! May the magical atmosphere fill your spirit with boundless Starlight cheer!
I know only too well how that poor child must be feeling. There must be something we can do...

Allow me to once more express my gratitude, <split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)>. For your tireless efforts, and for restoring young Timothey's sense of wonder and joy, I thank you on behalf of all the saint's little helpers.

Welcome back to the Thaumaturges' Guild, <split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)>. Do not fear─I bear you no ill will for investigating the allegations against me. Rather, I thank you for absolving me of any suspicion of wrongdoing.

I am currently collating the evidence regarding my ability to divine a man's capabilities: the notes I made upon first meeting each initiate, and those made over the courses of their careers─some long, some short. I shall be taking a keen interest in your own progress.
One...one day at a time. That's the only way we can live, isn't it? Live...and try to do better.
I do wish my son could pursue his dreams... Yet I cannot help but fear what will become of him after I am gone.
Have ye come for books? Or are ye just here to sniff about G'jusana!?
It ain't like to be easy, but I'll make G'jusana a free woman again, so I will!
There is always more left to learn, my friend. After all, he who strives to better his craft grows through greater challenge.

Another storm has come and gone. These moments of peace never last long though, do they?
I am painfully aware of the hypocrisy of our request, and the self-inflicted nature of our predicament.
But should it serve to deliver my people from their unkind fate, gladly shall I bow my head and beg for aid. I expect─nay, welcome─the coming storm of scorn and disdain.
Nidhogg... He is the source of our suffering. If we do not fell the wyrm, these endless clashes count for naught.
If Marshal Tarupin is to be believed, the smallfolk will not be so easily deceived. At the very least, it should be safe for the Warrior of Light to travel with impunity.
We must not give in to despair, <split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)>. We will prevail. The dawn's light will shine again...
No matter how long it takes, I have faith we will find the others! With Lady Yugiri's shinobi, Urianger's intelligence, and my...versatility, there's nothing we cannot do!

The Agrius is a wonder to behold, but even that miracle of engineering was humbled by the mighty Midgardsormr. I've lost count of the hours I've spent gazing upon this deadly embrace, imagining the titanic contest that led to their mutual demise...
I keep telling the grown-ups that we're adventurers now, but they still won't let us out to explore. They say it's “too dangerous.”
We'll just have to show them what the Doman Braves are capable of...

La-la-lah! La-di-dah-di-dah!♪
A child's joy will always brighten your day!♪
I'll show you a smile if you're happy to pay!♪
Did that sound right? Tataru has been teaching me traditional Ul'dahn rhyming songs. The children of Ul'dah seem to spend an awful lot of time thinking about money...
I like going to visit Rowena─she always has lots of interesting things in her store. Sometimes, though, I wonder why she needs to stock so much junk. ...Well, that's what it looks like to me, anyway!
I'm buying herbs to make into poultices. People are always getting hurt around here, you see, and you can never have enough medicine. A Doman Brave is always prepared!
Have you witnessed the scene over yonder? Such is the fate of he who would toy with women's hearts. Let us see how Thancred's silver tongue wags its way out of this one...
In Doma, fidelity is a highly prized virtue. Perhaps it is a difference in culture, but this...situation lies outside my comprehension.

Our every waking moment is consumed with the search for a viable means by which the Ascians might truly be destroyed.  While our efforts are thus occupied, I am certain Alphinaud will appreciate any support you can offer the Crystal Braves.

When first we laid the foundations, never did I imagine that we would receive an Ishgardian envoy here at the Rising Stones. 'Tis a refreshing reminder of how the world we take for granted can shift so quickly and completely...
I pray that Moenbryda's experiments will soon support the possibilities inherent in her theories...
We shall press onwards, as we have always done─I will not squander the sacrifices of our fallen friends by surrendering to a paralysis born of fear.
We have had reports from a number of frontier settlers... 'Twould seem the dragons have come as far as Mor Dhona.

'Tis impossible to predict how many will rally to Ishgard's call for reinforcements...
I do not envy those responsible for planning the city's defense.
You are a welcome sight, as always, <split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)>. I thank the Twelve not only for Ishgard's salvation, but also your safe return.
When one is in need of precious commodities, it helps to have friends in the right places. Fortunately, I am well acquainted with the charming daughter of a successful Ul'dahn import merchant.
We needed a rare ore to modify the white auracite, and Thancred solved the problem using only his linkpearl. I mean, it's great and everything, but where's the fun in that...?
Moenbryda has charged us with acquiring some rather esoteric manuscripts, but I'm afraid the task is proving to be nigh impossible...
When the city of learning was abandoned, a great many tomes were scattered and lost. How smoothly our research might proceed were we able to peruse the archives of yesteryear.

These two have been telling me stories about the corrupted crystal formations that appeared following the Calamity. I'll need more data before I can draw a conclusion, but I'm intrigued by the potential of their untapped energies.
Hello, ObjectParameter(1), ,1)>! Are you sleeping well? You must be absolutely exhausted from saving the realm on a daily basis!
Ever since Moenbryda arrived, the Rising Stones has been buzzing with excited energy. I must admit, her enthusiasm is rather contagious.
We were but stripling adventurers the night we saw fire rain from the sky and a pillar of light scorch the heavens. What a sight that was, eh, Coultenet?

Hoary and I were in eastern Thanalan when the colossal shards of Dalamud pierced the ground. We stood witness to the subsequent explosion of aether, and watched dumbfounded as the swirling energy solidified into those twisted crystal structures that we now know so well.
I am unfamiliar with the dishes of the lands to the north. Perhaps once Moenbryda has concluded her current research, she might deign to share with me her culinary knowledge.

In hindsight, mayhaps sending a lady in my stead was not the wisest of decisions...
Ah, pray ignore my ramblings!

I traveled to Ul'dah to meet with Thancred's friend─the one who promised us that rare ore?─and she began cursing me with words I've only ever heard from the mouths of pirates. I still have no idea what she was so angry about...

We were able to locate those elusive manuscripts in the archives of the Thaumaturges' Guild. I had not spoken much with the new guildmasters, but thankfully they were quite willing to accommodate us in our search.

Though it may seem tedious when compared with the smiting of terrible foes, poring over crumbling scrolls is one of a Scion's most important duties. Without the illumination of knowledge, we but vainly flail at specters in the dark.
I'm pushing ahead with my research as quickly as I dare. The next time you face an Ascian, I would have you fight with the proper weapon in hand.

As the receptionist of the Rising Stones, 'tis my job to receive all manner of guests with due courtesy! I've had to memorize the political positions and military ranks of half a dozen different nations...
That lady knight from Ishgard cuts quite a gallant figure, doesn't she?
I must confess, the relationship between those crystal formations and the destruction of the Ascians quite escapes me...
Professor Lamberteint has published a thorough study on corrupted crystals and their properties. I highly recommend you procure yourself a copy of his work.
Considering the sudden arrival of foreign envoys and the like, preparing suitable meals at the Rising Stones can prove to be an interesting challenge.
We must find some means of protecting ourselves from Ascian intrusions. There must be a way.
I don't feel much like talking at the moment. If you could just...give me some time.
I loathe to see Yda in such pain, but I have not the words to comfort her. Can you imagine it? I, Papalymo, the one who has an eloquent comment for every situation, am at a loss for words...
The Rising Stones feels somehow colder. Moenbryda always carried with her such an abundance of warmth and cheer.
If you're looking for the Scions, they've already left for the Alliance nations. I do hope Ishgard will be saved...
Considering recent history, will there be any amongst the Alliance willing to aid the Holy See? Ishgard has few friends at the bargaining table...
The town has been calm through all this talk of war, but if those dragons come to Revenant's Toll there'll be panic aplenty, I'd wager.
Should events take a turn for the worse, we are fortunate that this settlement is such a popular crossroads for so many veteran adventurers.
Though I have never seen one myself, it is said that dragons lair just beyond the borders of my homeland...
I am faced by a merciless mountain of administrative chores! Thankfully, this is one battle I am well equipped to fight!
So, Minfilia has committed the Scions to Ishgard's cause, has she?
Though she makes her pronouncements with unshakable confidence, I can only imagine how agonizing it was for her to arrive at this decision. So many lives at stake...
The threat of war sows panic and confusion, and routine tasks can offer a calming stability─being sure the larder is properly stocked, for instance.
Ladies, please, this is no way to─ Oh, hello, <split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)>!
I was just, er, entertaining some friends! Ahahaha. Oh gods...

\\<snort> Hee hee...
Ahahaha! Oh gods! Make it stop! My sides are about to burst!
A primal shackles its faithful with the bonds of eternal devotion, but I fear the power Thancred wields over his admirers is rather more fickle.
Especially when each realizes she is not the sole object of his affection...

\\<sigh>
Do we not have more pressing matters to attend to?
Here at the Gold Saucer, we strive to make all your dreams come true─even the dreams you never knew you had! Tee hee!
Welcome to the Gold Saucer, honored guest. There's no end to the wonders within these halls─pray don't be shy about partaking in them!
Newcomer or veteran, the Gold Saucer has something for everyone. Why not cast your worries aside for the day and delight in the myriad diversions we have to offer?
Beyond this door lie Chocobo Square and Minion Square, homes to the heart-pounding, hair-raising spectacles that are chocobo racing and Lord of Verminion.
My companion promised to meet me in Wonder Square, but she's nowhere to be seen! Do you think it's this fragrance I'm wearing? She's always had a most sensitive nose...
My companion promised to meet me in Wonder Square, but I can't find him anywhere! Do you think it's my dress? He's so particular when it comes to fashion...
If you've not yet done so, you must try wading in the water here. It's remarkably refreshing!
\\ All these bright lights and loud noises. I find it all so dreadfully...tedious. Or perhaps you've come to amuse me?
...No? Then go off and play your silly games, or whatever it is you've come to do. \\<sigh>
Welcome, honored guest, to the Manderville Lounge. On behalf of Master Godbert, we shall do all in our power to see that your stay is a pleasant one.
Should you be looking to return to Entrance Square, this passage will lead you there.
This passage leads to the chocobo racing course. Unauthorized entrance is strictly prohibited.
When post time draws near, we will provide further instructions. If you are looking to enter a race, please wait patiently within the halls of Chocobo Square.

Hey, name's Joe. Nice to meet... Wait, we met before? No...maybe not. Hmmm... I can tell you've got a story...and I reckon it's pretty interesting. Aye, I have a feeling that we'll meet again. Then, until we meet again.
Fond of Triple Triad, are you? I can't play enough of the game myself. I've defeated so many opponents now, they started calling me “King.”
And I must say, I've grown rather attached to the title. If you mean to topple me from my throne, then you'd best prepare yourself for a royal rumble!
...Stop. Before you utter a word, know that you address a Triple Triad champion. If you intend to challenge me, then pray do so only once your skills have reached their peak.
Until then, mayhap Jonas of the Three Spades would provide you with a less...daunting adversary.
